result.name: Tequila Jack's

reviews.text: My friends love this place and it is quite nice to sit at, but honestly this like barely qualifies as Mexican food. I'd go to almost any other Mexican restaurant in HK over this one. I think this place survives on people who don't know what Mexican food tastes like.

Great place to sit, enjoy good food and wine and chat with friends. Wide menu and staff seemed friendly enough, if not a little pushy for us to order more drinks.  Also the evening was overshadowed by their Amex machine ‘not working’ despite advertising...
Mostly a good experience.
Food was mediocre but it was cheap. Go there to drink. For better Mexican food close by, go to CaliMex or Caliente.

Great food (tried tacos and quesadillas and both were good), good drinks and nice staff. 

Good times!

Me and my partner have been here several times. Usually we love this place. But i have to give 1 star for two reasons.

First, neither myself nor my partner drink alcohol and when we come here, we don't usually order any other drinks either. But we have always felt that some of the staff here get annoyed and irritated that we don't order drinks. I don't know if management order them to act annoyed or irritated in order to pressure the customer or the staff work on commision, but it is an unpleasant experience. We love Mexican food and the openness of Mexicans. A shame the staff can't adopt the same warmth.

Second, i don't know if this is connected to the drink situation, but the portions are now smaller. We ordered the fried chicken because we know it's usually juicy with a good amount of meat. This time, the chicken was suffering from anorexia and was dry. Very disappointing, considering our bill came to $261 for nachos, chicken and a drink.

We won't be coming here again. If TJ's want customers to order drinks, they should say so. Me and my partner are happy to go elsewhere for our Mexican fix.
